    <text id="A7609T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Nadenbousch sends a quick note to his wife asking her to write him by "flag of
                    truce" if necessary.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-09-24"><abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 24/63</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Wife</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I am quite well have not heard one word from you since I left home. The people
                    here from our section of country are well</p>

                <p>Write me by flag truce if <orig reg="can't">can<hi rend="super">
                            <hi rend="underline">t</hi>
                        </hi></orig> otherwise My love to all friends</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours ever</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="John Quincy Adams">J Q A</abbr> Nadenbousch</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Carried by the kindness of a friend who visits an ill
                            relation<lb/><abbr expan="John Quincy Adams Nadenbousch"
                    >JQAN</abbr></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
